Description: Fast, safe and extensible Markdown to (X)HTML parser written in Ruby
 Redcarpet is Ruby library for Markdown processing that smells like
 butterflies and popcorn.
 .
 Redcarpet used to be a drop-in replacement for Redcloth. This is no
 longer the case since version 2 -- it now has its own API, but retains
 the old name. Yes, that does mean that Redcarpet 2 is not
 backwards-compatible with the 1.X versions.


